JUST ANOTHER JUMBOTRON DANCE PARTY
  Since the home screen is the first thing the client's users will see, it is really important to show big important information right away and to draw attention to it.  Enter the "Jumbotron".
  
  Billy's client just started hosting weddings at the winery and expects it to give the business a big boost so he wants extra attention to it.  Billy figured that he would place an image of a vineyard wedding in the Jumbotron with a call to action.  
  
<div class="jumbotron">
  <img src="..." alt="..."/>
  <p><a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="#" role="button">Learn more</a></p>
</div>
    
TABLES ARE DEAD.  LONG LIVE COLUMNS
  To keep the home page feeling sleek, billy decides that there will be a lot of whitespace on the page.  Hey Billy, why not mention the upcoming tasting event, snippet of the vineyards history, and that other special thing they were talking about?
  
    Long gone are the days when tables are needed to align elements on a page.  With Bootstrap you can now use the "ROW" class to align elements to the grid.
    
